text: Staff had his back facing the counter, so I had to call out to him before he noticed I wanted to order. Besides that, chicken tom yum was all right with tender pieces of thigh meat. Just wish the soup was piping hot.

Food was disappointing. Ordered pandan chicken only to unwrap a small piece of overcooked hard and dry chicken meat that's not edible. Tom yum chicken soup flavour was ok but chicken used is stale with strong frozen chicken taste. Will never buy any food from this outlet again.
40 minutes wait with no people in queue. Pricey pad thai which was "wet" and greasy made with tofu cubes instead of taukwa. Did not taste authentic!
Delicious Thai food, good presentation. Order the Tom yum mama noodle to share for 2 pax. It is like the famous one in Bangkok. Lots of seafood and noodles. Spicy level is just right.
Chicken was not cooked thoroughly (got the raw taste). Staff insisted that it is the marinate and that it's fully cooked.
